How It Works
The user selects a file.
The frontend sends the file to the backend.
The backend uploads the file to IPFS through Pinata.
Pinata returns a unique CID.
MetaMask requests transaction approval.
The smart contract stores the CID and metadata on the blockchain.
The uploaded file can be accessed through its IPFS CID.

